==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Paramagnetism
<hw>Par`a*mag"net*ism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Physics)</fld> <def>A property of materials which are not
magnetized in the absence of an external magnetic field, but in which
the magnetic moments of their constituents align with and enhance an
applied magnetic field; the induced magnetic field of the substance is
in direct proportion to the strength of the applied magnetic field; --
opposed to <ant>diamagnetic</ant> and contrasted with
<contr>ferromagnetic</contr>.</def> <rj><au>Faraday.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Paramaleic</ent>⟦br⟧
